<section id="about" class="fade-in">
  <span class="sec-lbl" id="lAbout">About Assam</span>
  <h2 class="sec-title" id="aboutTitle">Gateway to <em>Northeast India</em></h2>
  <p class="sec-body" id="aboutBody">Assam, the gateway to Northeast India, is a land of extraordinary natural beauty, rich biodiversity and vibrant culture. Known for its majestic one-horned rhinoceroses, vast tea gardens sprawling across hillsides, and the mighty Brahmaputra river flowing through fertile plains, Assam epitomizes the untamed splendor of India. The state is home to Kaziranga National Park, a UNESCO World Heritage site, and boasts extraordinary wildlife alongside diverse tribal communities. From the misty hills of Meghalaya borders to the lush forests of Arunachal Pradesh, Assam serves as a cultural crossroads where Hindu, Islamic, Buddhist and tribal traditions harmoniously coexist. The state's tea industry, handloom heritage, unique art forms and authentic cuisine reflect centuries of history and adaptation. Assam represents India's eastern frontier with its progressive spirit, natural heritage and warm hospitality welcoming visitors to explore its treasures.</p>
</section>

